    public class MMODFrame
extends javax.swing.JFrame
    The MMODFrame object is the main GUI class for the Multi Missile Overview Display. This class creates the other GUI classes to be displayed as JPanels and facilitates internal communication between the GUI classes and the controller. This class is also responsible for starting the polling thread that dictates when GUI components are to query the model and update their displayed state.

        Parameters:

        pController - Reference to the MDSCSS Controller object

      • handleSubsystemFailure

        public void handleSubsystemFailure()
        The handleSubsystemFailure function is sent by the MDSCSSController when connection to one or more of the subsystems has been lost. This function sets the color of the connection indicators of all subsystems to yellow-orange and displays a warning to the user. This function also calls the resetView function on all GUI Classes, so that all user control is disabled until connection is re-established.

      • handleCodeRed

        public void handleCodeRed()
        The handleCodeRed function is sent by the MDSCSSController when connection to one or more of the subsystems has been lost and has not been re-established for over 5 minutes. This function sets the color of the connection indicators of all subsystems to red and displays an error to the user.

      • handleLaunchModeChange

        public void handleLaunchModeChange()
        The handleLaunchModeChange function is sent by the MDSCSSController when no alternative interceptor for assignment has been found while in forgiving control. This function sends an alert to the user to notify the operator that the system has been reverted to manual assignment mode automatically.

      • handleDetModeChange

        public void handleDetModeChange(java.lang.String id)
        The handleDetModeChange function is sent by the MDSCSSController when the detonation override mode for an interceptor has been changed automatically. This function sends an alert to notify the operator that the interceptor has been reverted to manual manual detonation mode automatically.

      • handleClosing

        public void handleClosing()
        The handleClosing function is called when the operator attempts to close the application. This function prompts the user if they are certain that they wish to exit the MDSCSS and kicks off close operations if the yes option is selected.

      • handleInitialUpdate

        public void handleInitialUpdate()
        The handleInitialUpdate function is called when the MDSCSS achieves connection to the subsystems. This function calls the initial update function of all GUI classes and coordinates the population of the interceptor and threat overview tables.

      • handleThreatDestruction

        public void handleThreatDestruction(java.lang.String pID)
        The handleThreatDestruction function is called by the MDSCSS when the TSS indicates that a threat has been destroyed. This function removes the threat from the threat overview table and notifies the theater map so that it may update the corresponding indicator.
        Parameters:
        pID - The id of the destroyed threat

      • periodicUpdate

        public void periodicUpdate()
        The periodicUpdate function is called by the MMODPoller every second. This function calls the update function for every GUI class so that they reflect the current model. This function also checks the MDSCSSController's forgiving control state and issues prompts to the user, when necessary, to approve/reject forgiving assignment and detonate operations.

      • ChangeSMCDSel

        public void ChangeSMCDSel(java.lang.String pID)
        The ChangeSMCDSel function is called by the interceptor overview panel when a new interceptor has been selected in the table. This function forwards the selection to the SMCD so that it may update its selection.
        Parameters:
        pID - The new selected interceptor to be displayed

      • ChangeIOverviewSel

        public void ChangeIOverviewSel(java.lang.String pID)
        The ChangeIOverviewSel function is called by the SMCD when a new interceptor has been selected. This function forwards the selection to the interceptor overview panel so that it may update its selected row.
        Parameters:
        pID - The new selected interceptor to be selected

      • forwardLaunchCmd
